** About Us **

At ** QCSGroup ** , we are a leading supplier of IT and communications
solutions to our clients nationally. We have been in business for over 25
years, using our skill and experience to provide our clients with a
competitive advantage.

** About the Role **

We are seeking a Junior Helpdesk Technician to join our team and assist us in
achieving our goal of making our Clients exceptionally happy. Reporting to the
Service Delivery Manager, in this role, you will handle first-level support
requests that come in from our Clients. You will be responsible for providing
exceptional customer service, managing queries through our ticketing system,
utilizing our Monitoring and Management tools, participating in project work,
communicating with internal and external stakeholders, identifying and
mitigating risks, and working within the wider team to provide exceptional
customer experiences.

** Responsibilities: **   
• Provide technical support to staff and clients via phone and email.  
• Troubleshoot and resolve hardware and software issues.  
• Install and configure software applications, printers, and network systems.  
• Conduct maintenance and updates on operating systems and business
applications.  
• Monitor and manage network systems to ensure optimal performance.  
• Work in a team environment to achieve goals and meet deadlines.  
• Work autonomously to prioritize tasks and meet client needs.  
• Maintain accurate records of support requests and resolutions.  

** Requirements: **   
• Understanding of support tools, techniques, and how technology is used to
provide services.  
• Knowledge of TCP/IP and basic networking.  
• Sound knowledge of operating systems, business applications, printing
systems, and network systems.  
• Ability to work both in a team and autonomously.  
• High attention to detail and a proactive, "get it right the first time"
attitude.  
Why Join Us?  
We're passionate about providing a workplace where you can thrive and grow
your career. We offer excellent career growth and promotion opportunities, an
easy-going environment and team culture where you'll love what you do, and a
proactive approach to ongoing training to help you develop life-long skills.

** How to Apply: **   
If you're looking to progress your IT career with a great company, apply now
via SEEK with your CV and a cover letter addressing why you'd be a great fit
for the role. We look forward to welcoming you!

